In a televised speech to the Russian people, President Vladimir Putin confirmed that Russia now recognizes two breakaway regions in eastern Ukraine as independent. The signing of the recognition decree was then broadcasted live. Putin has also signed friendship and aid agreements with the leaders of the pro-Russian separatists in eastern Ukraine, AFP reports. Biden Condemns Putin’s Recognition Of Ukraine Breakaway… Canada To Give $500m Loan, Send $7.8m In Lethal Weapons To… The speech began with a long introduction by Putin in which he went through the history between Russia and Ukraine and, among other things, claimed that Ukraine as a whole was created by the Soviet Union. (SOURCE: NowayToday)